exterminate /ɪkˈstɜːmɪˌneɪt/

(exterminating,exterminated,exterminates) 

1. V-T To exterminate a group of people or animals means to kill all of them. 消灭 

例： A huge effort was made to exterminate the rats. 花了大气力来消灭这些老鼠。 

2. extermination N-UNCOUNT 消灭 

例： ...the extermination of hundreds of thousands of their brethren. …他们几十万同胞的灭绝。

